Unathi MsenganaIn her first interview since her surprise departure from Metro FM last month, Unathi Msengana has hinted at a disagreement with the station s bigwigs as one of her reasons for leaving. Speaking to Gareth Cliff on CliffCentral, Unathi said she did not regret her decision to leave. I don t feel pressure and that s why I just left radio. I was on some I don t like what s going on right now and I m not going to put up with it anymore because I m great at what I do, Unathi said.The Idols SA judge said it was important for her to bow out gracefully .There was speculation shortly before Unathi s departure that she was not happy with being paired with Khanyi Mbau on a mid-morning show during the radio reshuffle.Unathi however said she was not angry at the station s bosses, but pitied them because they do not know what it s like to be a DJ. Hate is a strong word. I pity them. There s a school of radio where we love each other and we re obsessed with radio and it s all we talk about, she saidReflecting on her life post-Metro FM, Unathi said that she was loving life at the moment, staying up late and drinking copious amounts of alcohol . I am ratchet! I m doing things that I never used to do. I love it, she said. TimesLive.